guideEyebrow: Things to do in Hurghada
guideTitle: Honest notes on the resort itself
guideIntro: >-
  Hurghada is a base, not a destination — and that's fine. Here's what's
  genuinely worth your time between sea days, from people who live here.
guideSections:
  - heading: On the water
    body: >-
      The reefs are the real reason to be here. A private boat to Giftun
      Island or the smaller reefs beats any crowded group excursion — you
      set the pace, you pick where to swim.
  - heading: For families
    body: >-
      Calm, shallow bays and short private boat trips work best with
      children. We keep days flexible so nobody's stuck on someone else's
      timetable.
  - heading: Best time to visit
    body: >-
      The Red Sea is good year-round; spring and autumn are the sweet
      spot for both sea and the inland day trips, before the summer heat
      makes Luxor hard work.
  - heading: In the evening
    body: >-
      The marina is the pleasant end of town for dinner. Beyond that, the
      best evenings we arrange are quiet ones — and the early night
      before a dawn start in Luxor.
guideLinkLabel: Read the full Insider's Guide →
